<p><strong>Explore Folk Arts at Amritsar</strong></p>

<p>Folk dances like Giddha and Bhangra are world famous because of their rhythm, energy and vivid dressing up. These dances are not only entertaining but represent scenes from daily life of a local. Then there is Gatka, a form of martial art presented very rhythmically. These folk dances and music are so indigenous, representing India at the very core.</p>

<figure class=" ">
  
  
</figure>

<p><strong>Azadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav and Amritsar</strong></p>

<p>So now you definitely know why I chose to speak of Amritsar today on ‘Azadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav’. Everything about the city; its history, geography, art and culture; is extraordinarily original; extraordinarily Indian.</p>
